{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1110,"text":"How many people here have heard of PMS?"},{"time":5429,"text":"Everybody, right?"},{"time":6915,"text":"Everyone knows that women\ngo a little crazy"},{"time":9399,"text":"right before they get their period,"},{"time":12270,"text":"that the menstrual cycle throws them\nonto an inevitable hormonal roller coaster"},{"time":16458,"text":"of irrationality and irritability."},{"time":19151,"text":"There's a general assumption\n"},{"time":20939,"text":"that fluctuations in reproductive hormones\ncause extreme emotions"},{"time":25858,"text":"and that the great majority of women\nare affected by this."},{"time":29391,"text":"Well, I am here to tell you\nthat scientific evidence says"},{"time":32150,"text":"neither of those assumptions is true."},{"time":34569,"text":"I'm here to give you \nthe good news about PMS."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38572,"text":"But first, let's take a look\nat how firmly the idea of PMS"},{"time":42242,"text":"is entrenched in American culture."},{"time":44634,"text":"If you examine newspaper\nor magazine articles,"},{"time":48210,"text":"you'll see how widely assumed it is\nthat everyone gets PMS."},{"time":52552,"text":"In an article in the magazine Redbook\ntitled \"You: PMS Free,\""},{"time":57940,"text":"readers were informed that between 80 \nto 90 percent of women suffer from PMS."},{"time":63520,"text":"L.A. Muscle magazine warned its readers"},{"time":66251,"text":"that 40 to 50 percent of women\nsuffer from PMS,"},{"time":69525,"text":"and that it plays a major role\nin women's mental and physical health,"},{"time":74169,"text":"and a couple of years ago,\neven the Wall Street Journal"},{"time":77160,"text":"ran an article on calcium\nas a treatment for PMS,"},{"time":80345,"text":"asking its female readers,"},{"time":82400,"text":"\"Do you turn into a witch every month?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":84989,"text":"From all these articles, you would think\nthere must be a mountain of research\n"},{"time":88866,"text":"verifying the widespread nature of PMS."},{"time":92790,"text":"However, after five decades of research,"},{"time":95948,"text":"there's no strong consensus\non the definition, the cause,"},{"time":100019,"text":"the treatment, or even \nthe existence of PMS."},{"time":104160,"text":"As most commonly defined by psychologists,"},{"time":107313,"text":"PMS involves negative behavioral,\ncognitive and physical symptoms"},{"time":112282,"text":"from the time of ovulation\nto menstruation."},{"time":115208,"text":"But here's where it gets tricky."},{"time":117420,"text":"Over 150 different symptoms\nhave been used to diagnose PMS,"},{"time":122661,"text":"and here are just a few of those."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124751,"text":"Now, I want to be clear here."},{"time":126632,"text":"I'm not saying women don't get\nsome of these symptoms."},{"time":129998,"text":"What I'm saying is that\ngetting some of these symptoms"},{"time":132622,"text":"doesn't amount to a mental disorder,"},{"time":135501,"text":"and when psychologists\ncome up with a disorder"},{"time":138822,"text":"that's so vaguely defined,"},{"time":141108,"text":"the label eventually becomes meaningless."},{"time":144591,"text":"With a list of symptoms\nthis long and wide,"},{"time":147563,"text":"I could have PMS, you could have PMS,"},{"time":150326,"text":"the guy in the third row here\ncould have PMS,"},{"time":152880,"text":"my dog could have PMS.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":156193,"text":"Some researchers said\nyou had to have five symptoms."},{"time":158861,"text":"Some said three."},{"time":160426,"text":"Other researchers said that symptoms\nwere only meaningful"},{"time":163282,"text":"if they were highly disturbing to you,"},{"time":165116,"text":"but others said minor symptoms\nwere just as important."},{"time":168669,"text":"For many years, because\nthere was no standardization"},{"time":171571,"text":"in the definition of PMS,"},{"time":173660,"text":"when psychologists tried\nto report prevalence rates,"},{"time":176725,"text":"their estimates ranged\nfrom five percent of women"},{"time":179512,"text":"to 97 percent of women,"},{"time":181810,"text":"so at the same time almost no one\nand almost everyone had PMS."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187638,"text":"Overall, the weaknesses in the methods\nof research on PMS have been considerable."},{"time":194330,"text":"First, many studies asked women\nto report their symptoms retrospectively,"},{"time":199967,"text":"looking to the past and relying on memory,"},{"time":202684,"text":"which is known to inflate reporting of PMS"},{"time":205865,"text":"compared to what's called\nprospective reporting,"},{"time":209230,"text":"which involves keeping\na daily log of symptoms"},{"time":211426,"text":"for at least two months in a row."},{"time":213864,"text":"Many studies also exclusively focused\non white, middle-class women,"},{"time":218833,"text":"which makes it problematic\nto apply study findings to all women."},{"time":223479,"text":"We know there's a strong\ncultural component to the belief in PMS"},{"time":227517,"text":"because it's nearly unheard of\noutside of Western nations."},{"time":231139,"text":"Third, many studies failed\nto use control groups."},{"time":235400,"text":"If we want to understand\nthe specific characteristics"},{"time":238210,"text":"of women who have PMS,"},{"time":239730,"text":"we need to be able to compare them\nto women who don't have PMS."},{"time":243932,"text":"And finally, many different types\nof questionnaires were used"},{"time":247160,"text":"to diagnose PMS, focusing\non different symptoms,"},{"time":251170,"text":"symptom duration and severity."},{"time":253823,"text":"To do reliable research on any condition,"},{"time":256934,"text":"scientists must agree\non the specific characteristics"},{"time":259883,"text":"that make up that condition"},{"time":261636,"text":"so they're all talking\nabout the same thing,"},{"time":263749,"text":"and with PMS, this has not been the case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267185,"text":"However, in 1994,"},{"time":269461,"text":"the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual\nof Mental Disorders,"},{"time":273129,"text":"known as the DSM, thankfully --"},{"time":275428,"text":"it's also the manual\nfor mental health professionals --"},{"time":279306,"text":"they redefined PMS as PMDD,"},{"time":283230,"text":"Premenstrual Dysphoric Disorder."},{"time":286248,"text":"And dysphoria refers to\na feeling of agitation or unease."},{"time":292192,"text":"And according to these new DSM guidelines,"},{"time":295652,"text":"in most menstrual cycles in the last year,"},{"time":298879,"text":"at least five of 11 possible symptoms"},{"time":302130,"text":"must appear in the week\nbefore menstruation starts;"},{"time":305822,"text":"the symptoms must improve\nonce menstruation has begun;"},{"time":309189,"text":"and the symptoms must be absent\nthe week after menstruation has ended."},{"time":315101,"text":"One of these symptoms must come\nfrom this list of four:"},{"time":318429,"text":"marked mood swings, irritability,\nanxiety, or depression."},{"time":323677,"text":"The other symptoms could come\nfrom the first slide"},{"time":326509,"text":"or from those on the second slide,"},{"time":328646,"text":"including symptoms like\nfeeling out of control"},{"time":331269,"text":"and changes in sleep or appetite."},{"time":334938,"text":"The DSM also required now\nthat the symptoms"},{"time":338815,"text":"should be associated with\nclinically significant distress --"},{"time":342995,"text":"there should be some kind\nof disturbance in work"},{"time":345828,"text":"or school or social relationships --"},{"time":348753,"text":"and that symptoms and symptom severity\nshould now be documented"},{"time":352259,"text":"by keeping a daily log\nfor at least two cycles in a row."},{"time":356276,"text":"And finally, the DSM required that\nthe emotional disturbance"},{"time":360131,"text":"should be more than simply an exacerbation\nof an already existing disorder."},{"time":365889,"text":"So scientifically speaking,\nthis is an improvement."},{"time":368675,"text":"We now have a limited number of symptoms,"},{"time":371322,"text":"and a high impact on functioning\nthat's required,"},{"time":374898,"text":"and the reporting and timing of symptoms\nhave both become very specific."},{"time":380354,"text":"Well, using this criteria"},{"time":383164,"text":"and looking at most recent studies,"},{"time":385310,"text":"we see that on average,"},{"time":386925,"text":"three to eight percent of women\nsuffer from PMDD."},{"time":392890,"text":"Not all women, not most women,"},{"time":395470,"text":"not the majority of women,\nnot even a lot of women:"},{"time":398240,"text":"three to eight percent."},{"time":400926,"text":"For everyone else, variables\nlike stressful events or happy occasions"},{"time":405883,"text":"or even day of the week"},{"time":407927,"text":"are more powerful predictors of mood\nthan time of the month,"},{"time":412012,"text":"and this is the information\nthe scientific community has had"},{"time":415452,"text":"since the 1990s."},{"time":416982,"text":"In 2002, my colleagues and I\npublished an article"},{"time":419722,"text":"describing the PMS and PMDD research,"},{"time":422856,"text":"and several similar articles have appeared\nin psychology journals."},{"time":427129,"text":"The questions is, why hasn't this\ninformation trickled down to the public?"},{"time":431540,"text":"Why do these myths persist?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":435116,"text":"Well, certainly the onslaught\nof messages that women receive"},{"time":438413,"text":"from books, TV, movies, the Internet,\nthat everyone gets PMS"},{"time":443557,"text":"go a long way in convincing them\nit must be true."},{"time":447190,"text":"Research tells us that the more\na woman believes that everyone gets PMS,"},{"time":452360,"text":"the more likely she is\nto erroneously report that she has it."},{"time":456268,"text":"Let me tell you what I mean\nby \"erroneously.\""},{"time":458544,"text":"You might ask her, \"Do you have PMS?\""},{"time":461270,"text":"and she says yes,"},{"time":462613,"text":"but then, when you have her \nkeep a daily log"},{"time":465031,"text":"of psychological symptoms for two months,"},{"time":467430,"text":"no correlation is found\nbetween her symptoms"},{"time":470704,"text":"and time of the month."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473016,"text":"Another reason for\nthe persistence of the PMS myth"},{"time":477385,"text":"has to do with the narrow boundaries\nof the feminine role."},{"time":480846,"text":"Feminist psychologists like Joan Chrisler"},{"time":483494,"text":"have suggested that\ntaking on the label of PMS"},{"time":487486,"text":"allows women to express emotions that\nwould otherwise be considered unladylike."},{"time":492919,"text":"The near universal definition\nof a good woman"},{"time":496310,"text":"is one who is happy, loving,\ncaring for others,"},{"time":499838,"text":"and taking great satisfaction\nfrom that role."},{"time":502694,"text":"Well, PMS has become a permission slip\nto be angry, complain, be irritated,"},{"time":507846,"text":"without losing the title of good woman."},{"time":511214,"text":"We know that the variables\nin a woman's environment"},{"time":515254,"text":"are much more likely to cause her\nto be angry than her hormones,"},{"time":518714,"text":"but when she attributes anger to hormones,"},{"time":521570,"text":"she's absolved\nof responsibility or criticism."},{"time":524337,"text":"\"Oh, that's not who she is.\nIt's out of her control.\""},{"time":527790,"text":"And while this can be a useful tool,\nit serves to invalidate women's emotions."},{"time":534406,"text":"When people respond to a woman's anger"},{"time":537127,"text":"with the thought, \"Oh,\nit's just that time of the month,\""},{"time":540122,"text":"her ability to be taken seriously\nor effect change is severely limited."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545480,"text":"So who else benefits from the myth of PMS?"},{"time":549467,"text":"Well, I can tell you that treating PMS"},{"time":551511,"text":"has become a profitable, \nthriving industry."},{"time":555992,"text":"Amazon.com currently offers\nover 1,900 books on PMS treatment."},{"time":562772,"text":"A quick Google search\nwill bring up a cornucopia"},{"time":565233,"text":"of clinics, workshops and seminars."},{"time":568971,"text":"Reputable Internet sources\nof medical information"},{"time":571874,"text":"like WebMD or the Mayo Clinic\nlist PMS as a known disorder."},{"time":576634,"text":"It's not a known disorder,\nbut they list it."},{"time":579141,"text":"And they also list the medications that\nphysicians have prescribed to treat it,"},{"time":583112,"text":"like anti-depressants or hormones."},{"time":586048,"text":"Interestingly, though, both websites\nsay that the success of medication"},{"time":591772,"text":"in treating PMS symptoms\nvary from woman to woman."},{"time":595859,"text":"Well, that doesn't make sense."},{"time":597590,"text":"If you've got a distinct disorder\nwith a distinct cause,"},{"time":600224,"text":"which PMS is supposed to be,"},{"time":602174,"text":"then the treatment should bring\nimprovement for a great number of women."},{"time":605982,"text":"This has not been the case\nwith these treatments,"},{"time":608536,"text":"and FDA regulations say that\nfor a drug to be deemed effective,"},{"time":612646,"text":"a large portion of the target population"},{"time":614713,"text":"should see clinically\nsignificant improvement."},{"time":617871,"text":"So we have not had that at all\nwith these so-called treatments."},{"time":621887,"text":"However, the financial gain\nof perpetuating the myth"},{"time":626200,"text":"that PMS is a common mental disorder"},{"time":629201,"text":"and is treatable is quite substantial."},{"time":633270,"text":"When women are prescribed\ndrugs like anti-depressants or hormones,"},{"time":636724,"text":"medical protocol requires that they have\nphysician follow-up every three months."},{"time":641833,"text":"That's a lot of doctor visits."},{"time":643806,"text":"Pharmaceutical companies\nreap untold profits"},{"time":646314,"text":"when women are convinced\nthey should take a prescribed medication"},{"time":650238,"text":"for all of their child-bearing lives."},{"time":653140,"text":"Over-the-counter drugs like Midol"},{"time":655764,"text":"even claim to treat PMS symptoms\nlike tension and irritability,"},{"time":660176,"text":"even though they only contain\na diuretic, a pain reliever"},{"time":664169,"text":"and caffeine."},{"time":666143,"text":"Now, far be it from me to argue\nwith the magical powers of caffeine,"},{"time":669579,"text":"but I don't think reducing tension\nis one of them."},{"time":673944,"text":"Since 2002, Midol has marketed\na Teen Midol to adolescents."},{"time":680510,"text":"They are aiming at young girls early,"},{"time":683340,"text":"to convince them that everyone gets PMS\nand that it will make you a monster,"},{"time":687585,"text":"but wait, there's something\nyou can do about it:"},{"time":689864,"text":"Take Midol and you will be\na human being again."},{"time":692926,"text":"In 2013, Midol took in 48 million dollars\nin sales revenue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699450,"text":"So while perpetuating the myth of PMS\nhas been lucrative for some,"},{"time":704100,"text":"it comes with some serious\nadverse consequences for women."},{"time":708320,"text":"First, it contributes\nto the medicalization"},{"time":710874,"text":"of women's reproductive health."},{"time":713544,"text":"The medical field has a long history\nof conceptualizing"},{"time":716748,"text":"women's reproductive processes\nas illnesses that require treatment,"},{"time":722158,"text":"and this has come at many costs,\nincluding excessive Cesarean deliveries,"},{"time":726268,"text":"hysterectomies and prescribed\nhormone treatments"},{"time":728978,"text":"that have harmed rather than enhanced\nwomen's health."},{"time":733675,"text":"Second, the PMS myth also contributes\nto the stereotype of women"},{"time":738505,"text":"as irrational and overemotional."},{"time":741871,"text":"When the menstrual cycle is described\nas a hormonal roller coaster"},{"time":745610,"text":"that turns women into angry beasts,"},{"time":748430,"text":"it becomes easy to question \nthe competence of all women.\n"},{"time":752775,"text":"Women have made tremendous strides\nin the workforce,"},{"time":755594,"text":"but still there's a minuscule number\nof women at the highest echelons"},{"time":759657,"text":"of fields like government or business,"},{"time":762397,"text":"and when we think about\nwho makes for a good CEO or senator,"},{"time":767343,"text":"someone who has qualities like \nrationality, steadiness, competence"},{"time":772462,"text":"come to mind,"},{"time":773971,"text":"and in our culture, that sounds more\nlike a man than a woman,"},{"time":777512,"text":"and the PMS myth contributes to that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781170,"text":"Psychologists know that\nthe moods of men and women"},{"time":784339,"text":"are more similar than different."},{"time":787172,"text":"One study followed men and women\nfor four to six months"},{"time":791235,"text":"and found that the number\nof mood swings they experienced"},{"time":794300,"text":"and the severity of those mood swings\nwere no different."},{"time":798154,"text":"And finally, the PMS myth\nkeeps women from dealing"},{"time":802357,"text":"with the actual issues\ncausing them emotional upset."},{"time":806374,"text":"Individual issues like\nquality of relationship or work conditions"},{"time":810809,"text":"or societal issues like racism or sexism\nor the daily grind of poverty"},{"time":815313,"text":"are all strongly related to daily mood."},{"time":818657,"text":"Sweeping emotions under the rug of PMS"},{"time":822420,"text":"keeps women from understanding\nthe source of their negative emotions,"},{"time":826272,"text":"but it also takes away the opportunity\nto take any action to change them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831640,"text":"So the good news about PMS"},{"time":834469,"text":"is that while some women get some symptoms\nbecause of the menstrual cycle,"},{"time":839205,"text":"the great majority don't\nget a mental disorder."},{"time":842758,"text":"They go to work or school,\ntake care of their families,"},{"time":845985,"text":"and function at a normal level."},{"time":848284,"text":"We know the emotions and moods\nof men and women"},{"time":851511,"text":"are more similar than different,"},{"time":853462,"text":"so let's walk away from\nthe tired old PMS myth of women as witches"},{"time":859097,"text":"and embrace the reality of high emotional\nand professional functioning"},{"time":863945,"text":"the great majority of women\nlive every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867149,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869425,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}